30:31.569 --> 30:37.215
undergraduate, you know, astronomy one type 
course, and that has hundreds of people. So

30:38.309 --> 30:41.373
there's some fraction that way. For a long time, 
there was a satellite called SME, the Solar

30:41.814 --> 30:56.916
Mesospheric Explorer, where undergraduates 
could actually go in and learn how to operate a

30:41.814 --> 30:56.916
spacecraft. And for a long time, we were the only 
university that was operating their own

30:57.597 --> 31:04.266
spacecraft, and we did it. with the proper 
supervision, but literally with undergraduate

31:04.786 --> 31:08.310
students. And the University of Colorado has also 
had a fair number of people go on into the astronaut

31:09.231 --> 31:18.080
corps. Alan Shepard and there are others. I don't 
want to start down the list because I'll surely

31:24.608 --> 31:28.752
forget one, but there's a bunch. um people are 
